<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Big Rain Ends Month-long Drought in East China's Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Heavy rain on the heels of a
strong typhoon has ended a two-month-long drought in east China's
Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The rains followed the Number 11 typhoon, known as typhoon
"Winnie" which hit east China on August 18. Precipitation in the
province averaged 110 mm over past three days since August 18.
</P>
<P>
After the rainfall, the water supply in reservoirs grew by more
than one billion cubic meters. The level of groundwater was also
rose, ensuring a sufficient water supply for both industrial and
farm production and people's daily life in the province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
