<DOCNO> XIE19970822.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Benefits from Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Investment Promotion
Center (IPC) of Tanzania has approved 883 projects to employ
146,488 people since the IPC was founded seven years ago.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Nasoro Malocho, Minister of State in the
President's Office (Planning) when he addressed the National
Assembly on Wednesday, according to a report reaching here today
from Dodoma where parliament is based.
</P>
<P>
Malocho said that the approved projects in the sectors of
agriculture, livestock, natural resources, industry, tourism,
mining and petroleum, finance and banks among others, are worth
over 2.4 billion U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Tanzanian government, in collaboration with the African
Development Bank, has completed a study to establish export
processing zones to make the country more conducive to investors,
Malocho also disclosed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
