<HEADLINE> Chicago Teamsters Contract Talks Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- United Parcel Service (UPS)
negotiators walked out of contract talks with a Chicago Teamsters
after all night talks on a contract for drivers and package
handlers in Illinois and Indiana, that is not covered by the
national settlement.
</P>
<P>
Most of the 185,000 Teamsters covered by the national agreement
are back on the job but UPS has sent out 15,000 layoff notices as
it waits to see how many shippers return with packages after the
15-day nationwide strike.
</P>
<P>
The International Brotherhood of Teamsters is holding victory
rallies and Local 710 is honoring their picket line.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Local 705 today says the main sticking point
remains the number of full-time jobs. Negotiations are scheduled
to resume Friday, The United Press International near West Side.
</P>
<P>
Negotiators earlier appeared to be making progress and
Waterhouse said bargainers had cut a list of unresolved issues
down to "about an issue and a half."  
</P>
</TEXT>
