<DOCNO> XIE19970822.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seeded Teams Advances at HK Beach Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 21 (Xinhua) -- All the four seeded teams
entered the quarter-finals after winning their opening-day group
matches at the four-day Kent Beach Volleyball 4-Men Grand Slam in
the Victoria Park here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
World number one Brazil won over Mexico and Iran with identical
2-0 to top the group A. Mexico took the second place after beating
Iran 2-0 and winless Iran was third.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champions United States outplayed China 2-0 and downed
India with the same scores to win the group B's top spot.
</P>
<P>
China, lossers to the Americans but defeated India, took the
second place and the winless India were ranked third.
</P>
<P>
Australia, seeded in Group C, ousted Hong Kong, China and South
Africa both in 2-0 to take the group .
</P>
<P>
South Africa were second and Hong Kong, China third.
</P>
<P>
Group D Seed New Zealand also entered the top eight with a 2-0
win over Japan and Indonesia, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Japan were second and Indonesia third.
</P>
<P>
Top two teams from the four groups qualified for the
quarter-finals, which will be played in two round-robin groups on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Top two teams from the two quarter-final groups advance to the
semi-finals while the third and fourth placers of the groups are
to play for the fifth to the eighth places.
</P>
<P>
The third placers of the preliminary groups are to play for the
ninth to twelfth places.
</P>
<P>
The 12-team tournament sanctioned by the International
Volleyball Federation and the Asian Volleyball Confederation,
closes on Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
