<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Hawkers to Defend Themselves in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Foreign hawkers in streets
here today said they will fight back if their South African
colleagues attack them in a planned anti-immigrant march.
</P>
<P>
Local media quoted a Nigerian hawker as saying they are going
to defend themselves if they are attacked during the
demonstration, scheduled tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
He said foreign traders will not sit and wait for the South
Africans to repeat what they did last time when they attacked
them, which resulted in the loss of thousands of Dollars of worth
of goods.
</P>
<P>
Last week, goods belonging to refugees and asylum-seekers
selling wares on streets of down town area were either stolen or
destroyed by members of the South African Hawkers Association and
other unemployed black people.
</P>
<P>
The association accused the foreign hawkers of inflating the
market prices.
</P>
<P>
Police have arrested about 180 people involved in the street
fighting.
</P>
<P>
South Africa's human rights commission has condemned the
actions, saying the looting and destruction of property must have
dented the country's image abroad.
</P>
<P>
According to the country's Ministry of Home Affairs, most of
the foreign hawkers are asylum-seekers waiting for clearance.
About three million illegal foreign immigrants are staying in
South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970822.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Results from European Swimming Championships (10-last) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Women's 4x100-meter freestyle relay final:
</P>
