<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congo (K) Refugees to be Repatriated From </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A tripartite agreement on
the voluntary repatriation of Congolese refugees from Tanzania
was signed by Tanzania, Democratic Congo and the United Nations
High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) here today.
</P>
<P>
The accord was signed by the Congolese Minister for
Reconstruction and Works Etienne Mbaya, Tanzanian Deputy Minister
for Home Affairs Emmanuel Mwambulukutu and UNHCR regional
representative for central Africa Darioush Bayandor.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, which will start soon after the signing of the
pact, will involve all Congolese refugees residing in Tanzania
even since the 1960s, Mbaya said during the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
He added that Democratic Congo has committed and is ready to
receive all Congolese from Tanzania so that they can contribute
to the reconstruction and development of their country which is
in peace now.
</P>
<P>
Bayandor said the UNHCR has already allocated sufficient fund
for the repatriation and that the fund can be added whenever
needed.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania is hosting a total of 74,000 Congolese refugees now,
according to Mwambulukutu.
</P>
<P>
Today's agreement was signed after the meeting between
Tanzanian President Benjamin Mkapa and Congolese President
Laurent Kabila during their meeting in Kinshasa on July 26-27
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
