<HEADLINE> Russia's Beloved Actor Yuri Nikulin Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia's best-loved film actor,
75-year-old Yuri Nikulin, also known as a clown, a circus director
and a TV personality, died in a Moscow clinic Thursday, according
to the Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Nikulin had to undergo heart surgery earlier this month, when
clinical death occurred. His heart had first stopped beating for 30
minutes during an operation performed to remove blocks from three
major heart vessels.
</P>
<P>
The doctors brought him back to life then but Nikulin's
condition remained extremely grave. They did "the impossible" in
the following 16 days to keep him alive, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Nikulin was a man of great talent, uncommon fate and
life-asserting force, and one of the most beloved personalities
for millions and millions Russian people.
</P>
<P>
Yuri Nikulin had a priceless gift of dispelling other people's
gloomy moods. He was "the soul" of any group of people with whom
he closely associated -- be it his family, friends, or television
shows.
</P>
<P>
It was said that Russia has been orphaned by the loss of its
beloved and inimitable actor Yuri Nikulin.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
