<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain Offers Emergency Aid to Montserrat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The British government announced
here today that it would provide emergency cash aid for those
Montserrat residents who want to leave the volcano-stricken
Caribbean island to nearby countries.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Department for International Development said today
that those adults moving to other countries in the Caribbean
region would get 2,400 pounds (about 3,840 U.S. dollars) over the
next six months, provided they did not have savings and assets of
more than 10,000 pounds (about 16,000 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Those people under 18 in the British colony would get 600
pounds (about 960 dollars) and the British government would also
pledge to pay air fares to nearby countries.
</P>
<P>
But the aid package was well short of the amount demanded by
the Montserrat government officials after new evidence showed that
the Soufriere Hills volcano could have a massive eruption in the
near future.
</P>
<P>
British International Development Secretary Clare Short was
quoted by the BBC television as saying today: "I understand that
people are disgruntled but we have acted very quickly and
reasonably.
</P>
<P>
"We provided funds for people who want to travel to Britain,
we're now announcing a package for people who want to relocate in
the Caribbean," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
