<HEADLINE> Jordan, PLO Call for Joint Arab Action for Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Top Jordanian and Palestinian
officials today called for joint Arab efforts to put back on track
the Middle East peace process that has been stalled since March.
</P>
<P>
It was important to continue the Jordanian-Egyptian-Palestinian
coordination and (the Arab countries') contact with the Israeli
side on the way of resuming peace to the region, Radio Jordan
quoted Jordanian Minister of Foreign Affairs Fayez Tarawneh as
saying.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks after meeting with visiting Chairman of
Political Department of Palestinian Liberation Organization (PLO)
Farouk Kadoumy who arrived here today for a brief visit.
</P>
<P>
It was urgent to intensify such joint efforts in support of
peace, as the tension in the region was accelerated by the July 30
suicide bombings in West Jerusalem which killed 16 people, said
the minister.
</P>
<P>
Kadoumy said joint Arab action was the basic element in facing
challenges presently blocking the peace process.
</P>
<P>
He added his visit came just in the framework of consultations
and coordination with Jordan with regards to the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The peace process has been stalled till now since Israel began
to build Jewish settlements in Arab East Jerusalem in March.
</P>
<P>
During the period of deadlock, efforts by the U.S. and Egypt to
reactivate the peace talks have failed due to Israeli government's
hardline policy. 
</P>
