<DOCNO> XIE19970822.0034 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF Approves Cameroun's Economic Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary Fund
(IMF) has approved in Washington last night Cameroun's letter of
intent which outlines Cameroun's economic and financial program
for the next three years, according to Radio Cameroun here today.
</P>
<P>
The letter of intent, approved by the board of directors of
the IMF, was signed on July 24, 1997 by Cameroun's Prime Minister
Peter Mafany Musonge.
</P>
<P>
It is based on a policy to promote economic growth, reduce
poverty in the country and restructure the banking sector.
</P>
<P>
The approval of the plan will give Cameroun access to
reinforce structural adjustment facilities.
</P>
<P>
Cameroun's economic recovery is going on smoothly, with the
growth rate standing at 5 percent up from 3 percent a few years
ago.
</P>
<P>
More foreign capital will be attracted to the country with the
approval of the letter of intent. Privatization will be further
encouraged, thus paving way for further boosting the economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
