<HEADLINE> SADC, EU Ministers to Meet in Vienna Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Cabinet ministers from the
Southern African Development Community (SADC) will meet their
counterparts from the European Union next year in Vienna, Austria
to deliberate on regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Out-going Austrian ambassador to Zimbabwe Felix Mikl today
told the Zimbabwe News Agency the meeting to be held in the
second half of next year will also discuss relations after the
Lome Convention expires in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Mikl said more emphasis is now being placed on regional rather
than bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Regional integration, he said, requires certain sacrifices on
the part of national government.
</P>
<P>
Austria assumes the presidency of the European Union next
year.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Mikl bade farewell to Zimbabwe's Vice-president Joshua
Nkomo at his office as he ends his term of duty in the country
this month. 
</P>
