<HEADLINE> Liberia Facing Serious Financial Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Liberia's newly-installed
president Charles Taylor today said his country is facing serious
financial difficulties and urged the international community to
aid.
</P>
<P>
According to Taylor, the Liberian government has to deal with
the salary arrears owed to public servants which amount to 1.12
million Liberian dollars (about 30,000 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
What's more, the government is facing a foreign debt of three
billion U.S. dollars and a domestic debt of two million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The president called on the International Monetary Fund and
other financial organizations to do what they have promised to
provide Liberia with financial assistance after the seven-year
civil war is over.
</P>
<P>
He also urged Liberians to make sacrifice for the good of the
country when the nation is suffering from difficulties.  
</P>
</TEXT>
