<HEADLINE> Further Measures Adopted to Expedite Supplies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Iraq Sanctions
Committee said today it had adopted further measures to expedite
processing of humanitarian supplies to Iraq.
</P>
<P>
To expedite further the processing of applications to ship
humanitarian goods to Iraq under Security Council resolution
986, the form of "Notification or Request to Ship Goods to Iraq"
and the "guidance note" on its completion have been revised. A
copy of the revised form and guidance note would be circulated to
all member states shortly, said the committee.
</P>
<P>
It said that to facilitate the delivery of humanitarian
supplies to Iraq, the initial validity period of all approval
letters to ship humanitarian supplies to Iraq will be extended
form the previous 120 days to 180, with a possible further
extension of another 90 days on request.
</P>
<P>
The committee said the measures were to be implemented by the
Secretariat as from September 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
