<HEADLINE> Forum Marks Books on Deng's Military Ideas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A forum to mark the publication
of a series of books on Deng Xiaoping's ideas on army building in
modern China opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The ten-volume collection contains nearly two million
characters.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, who is also general secretary of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
chairman of the Central Military Commission, wrote an inscription
for the books and called for further study of the late leader's
ideology and research into the characteristics and laws for army
building under new situations.
</P>
<P>
Other inscriptions were written by vice chairmen of the Central
Military Commission Liu Huaqing, Zhang Zhen, Zhang Wannian and Chi
Haotian.
</P>
<P>
China's opening-up and modernization should be guided by Deng's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, so as
to ensure the promising future of the country's socialist
construction, Zhang Wannian said in a speech.
</P>
<P>
The People's Liberation Army (PLA) must be unquestionably under
the leadership of the Communist Party of China, Zhang noted.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was presided over by Yu Yongbo, member of the
Central Military Commission and director of PLA General Political
Department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
