<HEADLINE> Triple Olympic Champion de Bruin Quits Euro Champs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Ireland's triple Olympic champion
Michelle de Bruin has withdrawn from Saturday's 200-meter
individual medley at the European swimming championships.
</P>
<P>
Irish team sources said it was her tireness to force her pull
out of the event after winning two golds and a silver in the first
three days of the championships.
</P>
<P>
But the 27-year-old Irishwomen still plans to defend her
200-meter butterfly title on Sunday, the sources said. So she
needed the extra days to prepare for it.
</P>
<P>
de Bruin, like other swimmers competing in the San Pablo pool
beneath the boiling sun, complained about the heat after winning
her second gold in the 200-meter freestyle on Wednesday and said
she was tired when she was beaten into second place in the
400-meter freestyle on Thursday. 
