fighting in Cambodia between government forces and those loyal to
prince Norodom Ranarridh in areas opposite Thailand's northeastern
Surin Province.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Chavalit told reporters that Thailand
welcomes humanitarian aid from overseas for the Cambodian
refugees.
</P>
<P>
The Cambodian co-defense ministers arrived in Thailand on
Thursday. earlier today they also met Thai Army Commander-in-Chief
Gen. Chettha Thanajaro. they will leave for home on Saturday.
</P>
