<HEADLINE> Judge to Collect Information on Terrorist Carlos in Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 22 (Xinhua) -- France's top anti-terrorist judge
Jean-Louis Bruguiere will go to the Hungarian capital Budapest
in late September to collect information concerning international
terrorist Illich Ramirez Sanchez, more often called Carlos, Agence
France-Presse reported today.
</P>
<P>
Bruguiere will seek data on the activities of Carlos and his
followers from 1979 to 1985 in Budapest, which served as their
pivoting station for carrying out guerrilla attacks in Europe, the
report quoted Hungarian intelligence service head Tamas Somogyi as
saying today in Budapest.
</P>
<P>
Born in Venezuela, Carlos was arrested by French intelligence
agents in Sudan in August 1994 and is expected to be put on trial
in Paris on December 12-19 for allegedly murdering two French
counter-espionage agents in June 1975 in Paris. 
</P>
