<HEADLINE> German Consortium Bids on Major Arms Deal with South Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A German consortium led by the
Thyssen group and Daimler-Benz Aerospace AG (DASA) today said it
had "very good chances" to win a multi-billion-U.S.-dollar arms
deal with South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Under the German bid, the companies are planning to build
corvettes, submarines, training aircraft and light transport
helicopters for South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Given South Africa's strained finances, the purchases, which
would cost over two billion dollars, are expected to last well
into the next century.
</P>
<P>
To win the deal, the German consortium has to defeat rival
bidders from Britain, France and Spain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
