<DOCNO> XIE19970822.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Accelerating State-Owned Enterprise Reforms (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The 14th National Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the third plenary meeting
of the 14th CPC Congress, which outlined China's market economy
development and set the goals for the state-owned sector were two
milestones in China's decade-long enterprise reform drive.
</P>
<P>
Since then, China has increased reforms in the state-owned
enterprises across the country, and adjusted the industrial
structure to keep the state-owned sector the driving force in the
nation's economy.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-minister of the State Economic and Trade
Commission Chen Qingtai has made these remarks, saying that the
purpose of the reform was to streamline the structure of the
state-owned sector and to establish a "modern enterprise system"
in some selected companies.
</P>
<P>
China is now experimenting with a new enterprise system in
2,598 enterprises, in a hope to spread their experiences in other
companies, he noted. The number of the pilot cities in an endeavor
of "optimizing capital structure" that is intended to adjust both
the industrial and product structures in enterprises, has
increased from 18 at the beginning to the present 58 and will be
111 by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
There were 1,099 enterprises in the 58 pilot cities that were
permitted to declare bankruptcy, and 1,192 that were merged with
other company groups. In the process, 1.23 million surplus
employees were diverted to other jobs.
</P>
<P>
Chen acknowledged that the overall strength of the state-owned
sector was strengthened in spite of the amount it shrank in the
country's economy.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of state-owned assets was 4.5 trillion yuan in
1995, 1.7 times the 1990 amount, he noted. State-owned enterprises
now hold 53.7 percent of the nation's total assets of industrial
enterprises, have 33.8 percent of sales income, 34.1 percent of
added value production, and 55.2 percent of pre-taxed profits.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
