<DOCNO> XIE19970822.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Retail Sales Drop Slightly in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A small decline in June sales
ended a strong quarter for Canadian retailers, Statistics Canada
said today.
</P>
<P>
In June, retail sales slipped 0.2 percent to 13.9 billion U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sales by motor and recreational vehicle dealers fell sharply in
June, dampening an otherwise strong month, the federal statistics
agency said.
</P>
<P>
In the second quarter, retail sales rose to 41.6 billion
dollars, up 1.6 percent over the previous quarter.
</P>
<P>
The latest quarterly increase compares with 2.1 percent in the
first quarter and 2.6 percent in the fourth quarter of last year.
</P>
<P>
Sales in the second quarter were 7.6 percent higher than the
same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that retail sales strength in the fourth
quarter of last year and the first quarter of this year occurred
as savings rates fell to record lows and consumer credit continued
to rise.
</P>
<P>
In the second quarter, however, the growth may have been
spurred by increases in employment as well as in wages and
salaries, according to the agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
