<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Praises Anti-Drought Success In Heilongjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Jiang
Chunyun has given high marks to the anti-drought drive waged by
northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, and says the lessons
learned from the experience need to be spread.
</P>
<P>
During a inspection tour of this leading grain base from August
19 and 22, Jiang, who is in charge of agricultural issues, said
that although Heilongjiang suffered a severe drought this year,
its grain output may be the same as last year's owing to the
redoubled efforts of the province in preventing drought.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he appreciated Heilongjiang's great success in grain
production in recent years; the province has had bumper crops for
the past seven years straight and a record grain output of 30
billion kilograms last year.
</P>
<P>
Vast areas in Heilongjiang were plagued by severe drought this
year, but the provincial officials said that they have worked hard
to reduce the disaster and a bumper crop is attainable if there is
no early frost.
</P>
<P>
The vice premier also stressed that the province should speed
up the industrialization process of agriculture, in a bid to make
farming a more profitable business.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by the top provincial officials of Heilongjiang,
Jiang inspected the grain fields in some counties in the province
and talked with local farmers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
