<HEADLINE> India Seizes 43 KG Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- In a major haul, the Indian
police seized 43 kilograms of heroin valued at 430 million rupees
(about 12.3 million U.S. dollars) in the international market late
Thursday night, Press Trust of India (PTI) reported today.
</P>
<P>
Four people have been arrested in connection with the
smuggling, PTI said.
</P>
<P>
Acting on the basis of intelligence reports, the police
intercepted a car on the Delhi-Uttar Pradesh border on Thursday
night.
</P>
<P>
Detailed examination on the vehicle led to detection of two
cavities under the front seats in which 43 kilograms of heroin
were sealed in 39 packets.
</P>
<P>
While three suspects were arrested on the spot, prompt
follow-up action led to the arrest of another suspect who was to
receive the consignment in Delhi. 
</P>
