<HEADLINE> Turkish President to Visit Hungary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel is to pay a two-day official visit to Hungary from
September 3 to 4, lcoal newspaper Daily News said today.
</P>
<P>
Demirel will be accompanied by a large group of Turkish
businessmen during his two-day visit at the invitation of his
Hungarian counterpart Goncz Arpad.
</P>
<P>
A senior diplomat from the Hungarian Embassy in Ankara
confirmed the report when asked by Xinhua, but he declined to give
any details about the visit.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish President will also open an exhibition to
display leading Turkish artists' works besides political talks
with Hungarian leaders during his stay in the eastern European
country, the newspaper said. 
