<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Sino-South African Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Tang Guoqiang said today that China is ready to work
with South Africa to ensure that the normalization of bilateral
relations goes smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remark here when asked to comment on a recent
statement made by South African Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo at the
Foreign Affairs Committee of South African National Assembly that
South Africa will sever its "diplomatic relations" with Taiwan and
establish comprehensive diplomatic relations with the People's
Republic of China by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
He also said that South Africa will follow the international
trend and act as the United Nations and other countries do in
dealing with the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome and appreciate Nzo's statement," Tang said,
stressing that China is willing to establish and develop friendly
relations and cooperation with South Africa on the basis of the
Five Principles of Peaceful Co-Existence.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China is also willing to settle specific
issues concerning the establishment of bilateral diplomatic ties
with South Africa through negotiations on an equal footing and
friendly consultations.
</P>
<P>
China clearly and consistently opposes the maintenance of
official relations or official contacts of any form with
Taiwan by countries which have diplomatic ties with China, Tang
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
