<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Namibian Deputy PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin in
a meeting today with Namibian Deputy Prime Minister Hendrik
Witbooi said that China is ready to advance its cooperative relations
with Namibia to a new height.
</P>
<P>
Since Namibia gained its independence, relations between the
two countries have witnessed an overall growth, with fruitful
results scored in a wide range of areas, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He described his exchange of visits with President Sam Nujoma
last year as successful, saying that they helped deepen mutual
understanding and trust and also laid a basis for establishment
of Sino-Namibian friendly relations in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang gave high praise to Namibia's pursuit of a national
reconciliation policy, and its devotion to the safeguarding of
social stability, economic growth and improving people's living
standard, saying that Namibia has scored commendable achievements
in its national development.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke well of Namibia's stance of good-neighborliness
and non-alignment, its active engagement in African issues as well
as its contribution to the peace, stability, unity and
cooperation in southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
Witbooi said China has supported Namibia in its struggle for
independence and consistently offered aid and assistance ever
since Namibia became a free nation. The Namibian government and
people will never forget this, he said.
</P>
<P>
He told Jiang about the second national conference of the South
West African People's Organization and the policies and measures
being taken to deal with problems facing Namibia, noting that it
is worthwhile to learn from China's development experience.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Witbooi expressed satisfaction with the smooth growth
of bilateral cooperation in different sectors, saying he hoped
that bilateral ties will be further strengthened and that
bilateral friendly cooperation will be more fruitful.  
</P>
</TEXT>
