<HEADLINE> Li Peng: China Major Force in Safeguarding World Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li
Peng said here today that China is an important force in
safeguarding the regional and world peace.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remarks in answering the participants' questions
after delivering a speech at the welcoming meeting hosted by
Malaysia's Institute of Diplomatic and Foreign Relations.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China has always advocated cooperation of mutual
equality and benefits, stressing that "we are pursuing an
independent foreign policy of peace."
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that there are some people in the world
spreading rumors about "China threat", which are "groundless".
</P>
<P>
China has concentrated on the economic construction, which
needs in particular a stable environment surrounding China, the
Chinese premier said.
</P>
<P>
He stated that even if China enjoys greater economic
development, it will pose no threat to any other country.
</P>
<P>
"China's military forces are defensive and would by no means
threaten any of its neighbors," he said, pointing to the fact that
China so far has no aircraft carrier.  
