<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With ROK Deputy Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
expressed his belief today that the good-neighborly and
cooperative relations between China and the Republic of Korea
(ROK) will surely move forward with the joint efforts of both
countries.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting here this afternoon with a ROK delegation led
by Kang Kyong-Shik, deputy prime minister and finance and economy
board minister, Jiang said China highly values the Sino-ROK
friendly ties, which are based on the Five Principles of Peaceful
Co-Existence.
</P>
<P>
The cooperative relations between China and the ROK in the
fields of economy, trade, science, technology and culture have
witnessed rapid progress since the two countries forged diplomatic
ties in 1992, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
The promotion of good-neighborly and friendly Sino-ROK ties and
the expansion of mutually-beneficial bilateral cooperation would
serve not only the fundamental interests of the two peoples, but
also the peace, stability and development in the Asia-Pacific
regions, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Kang Kyong-shik said that ROK-China exchange in personnel,
trade, investment and service industry has been "very active" in
the five years since the two countries forged their diplomatic
ties.
</P>
<P>
ROK-China trade volume last year totaled nearly 20 billion US
dollars and China has become the ROK's the third largest trade
partner, Kang said, adding that the two countries are
complementary in their economies and bilateral cooperation would
enjoy a broad prospect.
</P>
<P>
Attending the meeting were were Zeng Peiyan, vice-minister of
China's State Planning Commission, and Vice-Foreign Minister Tian
Zengpei, and ROK ambassador to China Chong Wook Chung.
</P>
<P>
Kang Kyong-Shik and his party are here on an official visit to
China as guests of the Chinese government. They will also attend
commemorative events to mark the fifth forging anniversary of
Sino-ROK diplomatic relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
