<HEADLINE> Eight Nepalese Die of Encephalitis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of viral
encephalitis has claimed eight lives in the Terai districts of the
mid and far western development regions in Nepal, the official RSS
news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
As of the other day, a total of 62 patients had been admitted
to the zonal hospital, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The hospital has constituted a committee to mobilize finances
for helping the encephalitis patients, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
By mid-August, five had died of encephalitis and meningitis in
Jhapa district of eastern Nepal.  
</P>
