<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of Guangdong Telephones Subscribers Tops 10 million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The number of telephone
subscribers in south China's Guangdong Province has topped 10
million, up 1.13 million on 1990.
</P>
<P>
The province's 1:7 person ratio for telephones is
twice the national average.
</P>
<P>
The handling capacity of local telephone exchanges has grown
dramatically from 1.8 million lines in 1990 to well over 12 million
lines.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the handling capacity for mobile phone switching
systems stands at 2.8 million lines, or near 20 percent of the
national total. The number of mobile phone users in the province
also accounts for one-fifth of the national total to surpass 2.1
million.
</P>
<P>
Since 1978, the province has exerted great effort to develop
the local telecommunications industry, and opened the nation's
first opening analog mobile communications network in 1987.
</P>
<P>
The province poured some 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion US
dollars) into the sector over the past five years alone in order
to expand local wide-band, optical fiber, digital microwave and
satellite communications.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the sector has also introduced a variety of
communications services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
