<HEADLINE> Turkish Students Protest Non-recognition of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkish students who graduated
from Egypt's famous Al-Azhar University have lodged a protest
against the education authorities for not recognizing their
diplomas.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Daily News reported today that the students
have submitted a protest statement to the Turkish High Education
Council (YOK) to express their anger.
</P>
<P>
The YOK reportedly refused to recognize Al-Azhar's diplomas on
the grounds that the university severely criticizes Turkish
Republic's founder, Kemel Ataturk.
</P>
<P>
"Some 2,000 Al-Azhar graduates around Turkey have suffered from
the decision of the YOK," said the students' statement.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that many Western countries recognize the Al-Azhar's
diplomas, the statement called on the education authorities to
reconsider and abrogate their former decision. 
