<HEADLINE> Li Peng on South China Sea Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 22 (Xinhua)-- The proper settlement of the
South China Sea issue is conducive to regional peace and
stability, visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng said here today.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that China's policy on this issue is to shelve
disputes for joint development and properly settle the problem
through peaceful and friendly consultations in line with the
international law and the maritime law.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remarks in response to a participant's question
after delivering a speech on good-neighborly ties at a welcoming
meeting hosted by Malaysia's Institute of Diplomatic and Foreign
Relations.
</P>
<P>
He noted that due to historic reasons, there exist territory
disputes between China and some countries of the Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), which are left over by history.
</P>
<P>
"We are not willing to see this issue hinder the normal
progress of our relations with these countries. We wish to explore
ways of how to solve this problem through friendly consultations
and dialogues," Li said.
</P>
<P>
"Even some of the issues cannot be resolved at the present
time, they can be shelved and left to our next generations," the
premier added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
