<HEADLINE> Italian Soccer Team Faces Tough Match at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Host Italian team will have
a tough match against Britain on Friday evening and needs at least a
draw to ensure a berth in the quarter-finals of the 19th World
University Games.
</P>
<P>
The group competitions of the football tournament at the
Universiade will conclude on Friday with top two finishers of each
group qualify for the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
China is the first team to advance after two rounds. They trounced
Czech Republic 4-0 and beat Nigeria 2-1 to collect 6 points to
qualify.
</P>
<P>
The other seven qualifiers will be decided by the last round group
matches and the possiblities are left wide open.
</P>
<P>
In group A, Brazil and Italy placed one-two with four points each
from one win and one draw. Brazil ranks first because it scored more
goals than the Italian eleven.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will take on Iran while Italy plays Britain. All the four
teams in the group have the chance of advancing.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine lead group B with four points, followed by Marocco and
Japan with three points each. Ireland is at the bottom of the group
but still has the chance of qualifying if it can beat Ireland.
</P>
<P>
In group c, the Netherland and South Korea both have four points to
their credit. A draw of the match between the two teams will be
enough to send them in the last eight and at the same time sends South
Africa and Uruguay, each has one points from a draw against a defeat,
packing for home.
</P>
<P>
The other qualifier of group D will most likely be the United
States as it has already collected four points from one victory and
one draw. If the American team can draw or even beat the Chinese team
on Friday, it will enter the quarter-finals together with China.
</P>
</TEXT>
