<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Insurance Conference Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The fourth Asia Pacific Life
Insurance Congress (APLIC) was opened here today, providing a
forum for more than 8,000 life insurance practitioners from the
region to share their experience in the thriving insurance
business.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the region's largest
insurance conference, Donald Tsang, Financial Secretary of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), said: "We aim to
make Hong Kong a regional insurance center that meets the
insurance needs of the modern world of tomorrow."
</P>
<P>
He noted that Hong Kong being chosen to host the congress
signified a vote of confidence in the city as an international
business center.
</P>
<P>
Insurance is gaining importance in all the economies in the
Pacific Rim, Tsang said. In Hong Kong, the insurance industry has
advanced at double-digit rates for nearly one decade, making
increasingly significant contribution to local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Currently, insurance accounts for four percent of the Gross
Domestic Product in Hong Kong and employs 50,000 people.
</P>
<P>
However, he said, the penetration rate of insurance still fell
behind that in Japan, North America and Europe. Statistics from
the host of the congress, the Life Underwriters Association of
Hong Kong, show that only 40 to 50 percent of Hong Kong population
are life insurance policy holders.
</P>
<P>
"The growth potential of Hong Kong insurance market is great,"
Tsang said. The SAR government is set to launch the Mandatory
Provident Fund Schemes next year, the latest initiative to
strengthen the development of the insurance sector.
</P>
<P>
At the four-day congress, about 70 keynote speeches, workshops
and exhibitions will be organized, all focusing on the theme "The
New Horizon".
</P>
<P>
Some 50 renowned insurance professionals from around the world
will deliver speeches at the congress to share their experience
and skills among the participants.
</P>
<P>
The APLIC is held every two years in different cities in the
Asia-Pacific Region, with Singapore, Malaysia and Australia
playing host to the first three congresses. The next APLIC is
scheduled for 1999 in the Philippines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
