<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Less New Companies Established in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The number of new companies
established during the first half of the year dropped one percent
from the same period last year, and their total registered capital
plummeted.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department show that only 378 new companies were set up between
January and June this year, down one percent.
</P>
<P>
Their registered capital added up to 60.7 million patacas
(about 7.68 million U.S. dollars), down 60.4 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 percent of the new companies deal with such
business as wholesale and retailing, restaurants and hotels. The
others involve construction and public engineering, services,
manufacturing and finance.
</P>
<P>
Most of the new companies are small, with over 85 percent of
them each having less than 100,000 patacas (about 12,660 dollars)
of capital.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more than a dozen companies were disbanded during
the period.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the declining number of new companies is the
result of a sluggish economy that has lasted for more than two
years. Macao's economic growth was recorded at less than one
percent in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
