<HEADLINE> HK SAR Delegation to Attend APEC Meeting in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- An official delegation of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), headed by
Director-General of Trade Alan Lai, will depart for Canada on
Sunday to attend a senior officials meeting of the Asia-Pacific
Economic Cooperation (APEC), a press release said today.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first senior officials meeting of APEC
attended by the Hong Kong SAR government after July 1 handover. As
provided for under the Basic Law and agreed with APEC, the Hong
Kong SAR participates in APEC as a separate and independent member
economy, using the name "Hong Kong, China."
</P>
<P>
Major issues to be discussed from August 28 to 30 by senior
officials of APEC include trade and economic as well as technical
cooperation, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
Before the meeting, Lai will hold a number of bilateral
meetings with other member economies to exchange views on major
issues.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong SAR delegation comprises officials from the Trade
and Industry Bureau, the Financial Services Bureau, the
Immigration Department, the Industry Department, the Hong Kong
Economic and Trade Office in Toronto, and the Trade Department.
</P>
<P>
This will be the third Senior Officials Meeting under the
Canadian APEC Chairmanship. Senior officials will meet again in
November before reporting this year's work to ministers and
leaders of APEC member economies. The APEC ministerial and
Economic Leaders' Meetings will be held in Vancouver, Canada, in
November.  
</P>
</TEXT>
