<DOCNO> XIE19970822.0140 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-US Project Aims to Make Breakthrough in Petroleum Technology (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With its economy surging ahead at an annual growth rate of ten
percent or so, China has become a net petroleum importer. It is
vital for the country to maintain and increase oil production,
which stood at 158 million tons in 1996.
</P>
<P>
To do this, China needs to increase the rate of recovery in its
existing oilfields in east China which have hitherto supplied the
bulk of its crude.
</P>
<P>
The key to this, Fang said, lies in finding "by-passed" oil
pools between drying wells and seeing the details of geological
structure so that petroleum engineers will know what to do to get
oil out in a more efficient and economical way.
</P>
<P>
"And that is where the underground imaging technology is
needed," he said.
</P>
<P>
Laurel has largely played the role of project organizer so far
but will have a cutting-edge instrument available and become a
market leader in China once the device hits the market.
</P>
<P>
The five-year-old company acts as the sole sales representative
in China for 26 Western manufacturers of geophysical prospecting
and marine survey instruments as well as oil-related lab
equipment, of which 17 are based in the United States. The company
sold ten million US dollars worth of instruments in China in 1996,
from three million US dollars in 1993.
</P>
<P>
"Our company is not limited to serving as an equipment
distributor; it seeks to shorten the time and path for turning
technology into a commodity," he acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the U.S. and China are a good match in a venture
like this, Fang said "the United States has the most sophisticated
technology, while China is the most fertile land for this
particular technology to become a commodity for three reasons: it
needs the technology badly; it has a big contingent of competent
scientists; and the cost of doing field tests is relatively low
here."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
