<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Holds Talks With Namibian Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji, holding
talks this morning with Namibian Deputy Prime Minister Hendrik
Witbooi, said that China treasures its traditional friendship with
Namibia and attaches importance to the development of friendship
and co-operation with the African country.
</P>
<P>
The two officials discussed bilateral relations and other
issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that since China and Namibia established diplomatic
ties, political relations have been stable and firm and there have
been constant exchanges of high-level visits and more friendly
contacts between the two sides. China is willing to work with
Namibia to consolidate bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have maintained friendly consultations and
close co-operation and joined hands in safeguarding the legitimate
rights and interests of the developing countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin and Namibian President Sam Nujoma
exchanged visits last year, pushing the bilateral political
relations and friendly co-operation to a new level, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Speaking highly of the results of bilateral economic and trade
co-operation, Zhu said that there is still great potential for
co-operation and he believes that through joint efforts, the two
sides can increase co-operation.
</P>
<P>
He voiced his appreciation for Namibia's "one China" stance and
congratulated it on the success of the second national congress of
the South West Africa People's Organization (SWAPO) not long ago,
and the election of Witbooi as SWAPO's vice-president.
</P>
<P>
Discussing China-South Africa relations, Zhu said he
appreciates South African Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo's
reiteration recently that South Africa will sever its "diplomatic
relations" with Taiwan and establish diplomatic ties with the
People's Republic of China by the end of this year, and that it
will treat its relations with Taiwan as the United Nations and
other countries do.
</P>
<P>
Zhu pointed out that to forge normal relations between China
and South Africa is not only in the fundamental interests of the
two peoples but are also conducive to strengthening unity and
co-operation between China and the South African Development
Community.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his pleasure at visiting China and his appreciation
for the Chinese government's warm reception, Witbooi conveyed
Nujoma's greetings to President Jiang Zemin and the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He said his country will stick to a "one China" position and
support China's reunification cause, and expressed his
satisfaction with the development of bilateral friendship and
co-operation and his appreciation for China's firm support and
assistance to Namibia. He said he hopes that bilateral friendship
and co-operation will continue to be strengthened. 
</P>
</TEXT>
