<HEADLINE> 2 Dead, 200 Missing as Tidal Waves Lash Indian Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Two people, including a child,
were killed and about 200 fishermen reported missing as tidal
waves lashed the coastal resort town of Digha in West Bengal,
India, in the past two days, Press Trust of India (PTI) reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The fishermen had gone for deep sea fishing aboard 20 trawlers
and even the satellite communication system failed to trace them,
official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of an unidentified tourist and a child were
recovered after they were washed away from the Digha beach.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 25,000 people were marooned as over 600 acres of land
remained submerged under sea water. A total of 2,500 houses were
destroyed.
</P>
<P>
The local authority has asked tourists to keep off the Digha
beach.  
</P>
</TEXT>
