<HEADLINE> Weifang Attracts Substantial Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Weifang in east China's Shandong
Province has brought in 2.24 billion US dollars in overseas
investment over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
To date, the city has approved 1,634 overseas-funded
enterprises, with 985 operational enterprises contributing 760
million yuan in taxes by the end of June.
</P>
<P>
Overseas funds have mainly flowed into the industrial,
agricultural, hi-tech and service sectors, with 40 large-scale
projects involving investments of over 100 million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attribute Weifang's success to extensive
efforts dedicated to improve infrastructure, simplify registration
procedures, and strictly enforce relevant laws and
regulations. 
</P>
