<HEADLINE> 3 Killed in Sea Ambush in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Three fishermen were killed and
seven others seriously wounded Wednesday afternoon in a southern
Philippine bay when armed men ambushed them while at sea, the
Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said the victims were doing their usual routine of
fishing at Panguil Bay, Lanao del Norte province in northern
Mindanao, when they were suddenly approached by the ambushers
aboard another vessel.
</P>
<P>
Several fishermen in the area, who heard the automatic gunfire,
rushed ashore and reported the incident to the police.
</P>
<P>
The police said their findings indicated that the ambush might
have been staged by competitor fishermen who want to monopolize
the richness of the Panguil Bay area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
