<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Back in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen returned to Beijing this afternoon at the end
of a successful official visit to Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Qi's entourage including his wife Zhou Hanqiong, Vice-Chairman
of Inner Mongolia Autonomous Regional People's Government Yun
Gongmin, Assistant Foreign Minister Yang Jiechi returned to
Beijing aboard the same plane.
</P>
<P>
Greeting Qian and his entourage at the airport were Deputy
Secretary-General of the State Council Li Shuwen, Assistant
Foreign Minister Wu Tao, and D. Davaasambuu, charge d'affaires ad
interim of the Mongolian Embassy in Beijing.  
