<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Winds up Visit to Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen today ended an official visit to
Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day visit, Qian held talks with senior
Mongolian officials, including President Nachagyn Bagabandy, Prime
Minister Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan, and Minister of External
Relations, Skukher Altangerel.
</P>
<P>
Both sides pledged to continue the friendly relations between
the two countries, and in particular, to deepen trade and economic
cooperation based on equality and mutual benefits. 
</P>
