<HEADLINE> Chinese Farmer Creates Desert Oasis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Wang Xigang, a farmer in
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, has spent a
decade creating an "artificial oasis" covering more than 1,000 mu
(67 hectares) of desert.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who lives near a desert in Ningxia's Yanchi County, has
planted over 100,000 trees since 1987. His forest belt has
prevented drifting sand dunes and improved the environment in the
region.
</P>
<P>
He earned some 50,000 yuan (6,250 US dollars) in 1996 from
baskets made with tree branches, and has helped more than 100
families improve their standard of living by planting trees.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
