<HEADLINE> China Hailed as Hot favourite at Badminton World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jakarta, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese badminton team,
spearheaded by the women's world number one Ye Zhaoying, has been
tipped as the hot favourite to dominate the World Cup Badminton
Championships which are underway at the central Java city
Yogyakarta of Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
China, fresh from the Sudirman Cup World mixed team triumph
last May, has sent a strong team to fight the host Indonesia for
the supremacy of the sports.
</P>
<P>
Apart from world champion Ye Zhaoying, the Chinese team also
includes the women's double world champions Ge Fei and Gu Jun, the
men's All-England champion Dong Jiong, the men and women's world
championships finalists Sun Jun and Gong Zhichao.
</P>
<P>
The 200,000-US-dollar World Cup has attracted shuttlers from 15
countries and regions. The five-day event opened on
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
