Beijing Seminar on Tibetan Studies refuted various Western
arguments that the Chinese government has destroyed Tibet's
traditional culture by presenting evidence clearly showing that
Tibetan traditional culture is flourishing.
</P>
<P>
Professor Colin Mackerras, a Tibetologist who serves as the
president of Griffith University and director of the Modern Asian
Studies School in Australia, commented that "Tibetan culture is
stronger than ever before. (China-Tibet-Culture)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
