<HEADLINE> British Trade Delegation to Visit Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- An eight-man delegation from
Staffordshire in Britain will visit Uganda in October, reported
the local daily "The Monitor" today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will be the first to visit Uganda under an
on-going investment promotion partnership between the Uganda
Investment Authority (UIA) and the United Nations Industrial
Development Organisation (UNIDO).
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by UIA Thursday said
that the delegation will be most interested in construction,
textiles, auto-parts and second-hand industrial machinery and
manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
The British delegation will also be seeking opportunities for
entering into joint partnerships with Ugandan businessmen in
various trade and investment related areas.
</P>
<P>
While in Uganda, they will meet government officials as well
as representatives from various business organisations. UIA and
UNIDO are currently engaged in a joint program to target British
investment into Uganda and also to improve trade ties between
Uganda and Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
