<DOCNO> XIE19970822.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Hosts World's Largest Number of Land Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Egypt tops world countries in
terms of land mines on its territories, totaling 23 million,
Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
But at the same time, Egypt is yet reckoned the least of
countries prone to problems emanating from the mines, said the
report quoting the spokesman of the Economic Commission of Africa,
an affiliate to the UN, as saying in Addis Ababa.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman, whose name was not given, said there are nine
countries worldwide most suffering the existence of land mines,
with Egypt coming on top thereof.
</P>
<P>
"Mines in Egypt do not pose any noticeable menace to the
development process neither do they inflict any human damage as is
the case in some other countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
The UN official attributed it to the fact that such mines were
planted at a profound depth in unpopulated areas in the desert,
which entirely lessens the possibility of their explosion.
</P>
<P>
The millions of mines in Egypt mostly spread across the Western
Desert and Sinai, important battle fields during the Second World
War and the scenes for several Arab-Israeli wars.
</P>
<P>
But there are sporadic reports about casualties from stepping
on land mines in Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970822.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Botswana Bans Meat Importation From Zambia, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Botswana has banned meat and all
by-products imported from Zambia and Zimbabwe because of a recent
outbreak of foot and mouth disease in the two countries, the
local paper Post reported today.
</P>
<P>
Motshodi Reborokwe, Botswanan Director of Animal Health and
Production has urged botswanan farmers to move their livestock
away from the common border areas.
</P>
<P>
He said that livestock owners must ensure there is no
cross-border movement of animals.
</P>
<P>
Botswana will step up searches on motor vehicles crossing the
borders.
</P>
<P>
The disease was reported in Zimbabwe two weeks ago in the
southeastern town of Chiredzi.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, the Zimbabwean authorities said the
outbreak of the disease in the area has been under control and
more veterinary officers have been deployed to speed up
vaccination. 
