<HEADLINE> British Foreign Secretary to Visit Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook will visit the Philippines late this month on his first
official tour of Asia, the British embassy here announced today.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines is the third leg of Cook's four-nation Asian
tour, his first official trip to the region since taking office
last May, the embassy said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
Cook will fly in on August 29 after visiting Malaysia and
Indonesia, and then travel on to Singapore after ending his visit
here on August 31.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Manila, Cook will meet President Fidel
Ramos, Foreign Secretary Domingo Siazon and Defense Secretary
Renato de Villa, and give a speech to a business community.
</P>
<P>
Cook and Siazon are expected to discuss a wide range of issues,
including recent developments in Cambodia, the Asia-Europe Meeting
in London next April, and the welfare of overseas contract
Filipino workers in Britain.
</P>
<P>
During Cook's stay here, the two sides will also sign a
memorandum of understanding on cooperation against child abuse
between the two countries' police forces.  
