<HEADLINE> Joint-Stock Hydropower Company in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Lijiaxia Hydropower
Co. Ltd. has been set up as the Lijiaxia Hydropower Plant on the
upper reaches of the Yellow River went into operation.
</P>
<P>
The new company will try to raise funds for the further
development of hydropower resources of the Yellow River, the
second longest in China after Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Lijiaxia, the first interregional joint-stock hydropower
company in the Yellow River Valley, has formed the shareholders
committee, the board of directors and the supervisory committee.
</P>
<P>
The shareholders committee consists of representatives from the
China Northwest Power Group, and investment companies from
Shaanxi, Gansu and Qinghai provinces and the Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region. The company plans to divide profits according
to the ratio of shareholders' investment.
</P>
<P>
The plant, located in Qinghai Province and with a total
generating capacity of two million kw, is capable of generating
5.9 billion kwh of electricity a year. The central government,
Shaanxi, Gansu and Qinghai provinces, and the Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region jointly built the plant at a cost of five
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
China has announced a plan to construct 13 hydropower stations
to tap abundant hydropower resources on the upper reachers of
the Yellow River.  
</P>
</TEXT>
