<HEADLINE> Twenty Japanese Asked to Be Deported From Panama by Church </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Catholic Church of
Panama has demanded 20 Japanese of a religious group be deported
for their illegal preaching.
</P>
<P>
The top hierarchy of the Catholic Church got together with
Panamanian Interior and Justice Minister Raul Montenegro on
Wednesday to examine the activities of the group, the "Moon," in
Panama.
</P>
<P>
Panama archbishop Jose Dimas Cedeno said the group is a
religious sect that divides and confounds the Panamanian people.
</P>
<P>
