<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets with Malaysian Deputy Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Deputy Prime
Minister Anwar Ibrahim and his wife today went especially to see
visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng and his wife at the hotel where
they are staying during Li's four-day official visit here.
</P>
<P>
Briefing Li on the recent financial crisis in Southeast Asia,
Anwar, also minister of finance, said China has a sound basis for
its economy and owns a lot of foreign reserves.
</P>
<P>
This is conducive to the stable development of China's economy
and beneficial to its economic and trade cooperation with foreign
countries, Anwar said.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said, "The economic and trade cooperation between China
and Malaysia has a solid basis. I hope the two countries should in
the future take a far-reaching perspective and a down-to-earth
manner to further promote their bilateral economic and trade
cooperation."
</P>
<P>
During the 30-minute meeting, the two sides also exchanged
views on other issues of common interest, especially the world
economy and international finance.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that as the current world economy has been
multi-polarized, the international currencies should also tally
with the need of the times subsequently.
</P>
<P>
Later today, Li will confer with Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohammad on promoting the bilateral relations and on
other issues of common concern. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
