<HEADLINE> China's Achievements Great, But Difficulty Remains, Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li
Peng said today that China has made great strides in economic
development since it began to carry out the policy of reforms and
opening-up to the rest of the world at the end of the 1970s.
</P>
<P>
But there are still many difficulties which need to be solved
as the country presses ahead in its economic drive, Li said in a
speech at a welcoming meeting here hosted by the Institute of
Diplomatic and Foreign Relations of Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
In the speech entitled "Toward a Relationship of Friendship and
Good-Neighborliness Geared to the 21st Century," the Chinese
premier briefed his audience on China's economic development and
made a few observations on the further development of amicable
cooperation between China and ASEAN countries.
</P>
<P>
"Beginning in the late 1970s, China entered a new historical
period of reform, opening-up and modernization. Over the past 19
years, China has all along kept a good momentum of economic growth
and the quality of people's life has improved noticeably, " Li
said.
</P>
<P>
He said that breakthroughs have been made in China's economic
restructuring aimed at establishing a socialist market economy and
the pattern of opening-up has basically taken shape.
</P>
<P>
"In recent years, as a result of strengthened macro economic
control by the government, we have brought under control inflation
which was once quite serious and ushered in a favorable situation
characterized by high growth rate, low price hikes and smooth and
coordinated growth of the national economy, " the Chinese premier
said.
</P>
<P>
China has formulated development plans for the last five years
of this century and on longer-range objectives to the year 2010,
he said, adding that implementation of these plans in the past two
years has been quite good.
</P>
<P>
"Our objective is, through the two switches in economic system
and mode of economic growth, to carry out the strategies of
revitalization through science and technology and of sustainable
development and to unswervingly implement the policy of opening-up
with a view to realizing economic development and all-round social
progress, " Li said.
</P>
<P>
He continued that China will keep its economic growth rate at
over 8 percent in the last five years of this century and over 7
percent in the first ten years of the next century.
</P>
<P>
"Yet we are quite clear that as we press ahead, there are still
many difficulties, especially given the fact that China has a
large population and weak economic foundation, " the Chinese
premier said.
</P>
<P>
"China is still at a rather low level in per capita terms even
compared with certain developing countries in Asia. We need to
work very hard for several more decades in order to realize
modernization and attain the level of averagely developed
countries," Li said, "We are confident that guided by the theory
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics initiated by
Deng Xiaoping, we are bound to attain the goal of modernization in
China." 
</P>
</TEXT>
