<HEADLINE> OSCE Discusses Crisis of Bosnian Serb Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The standing committee of
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) today
discussed the crisis facing the Republic of Srpska.
</P>
<P>
Lars Vissing, chairman of OSCE's permanent council, told a
press conference that the organization supports in principle the
scheduled election in the Republic of Srpskac, but hadn't reached
agreement on how to supervise the election.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources here blamed Russia for the failure to reach
an agreement.
</P>
<P>
Biljana Plavsic, president of the Republic of Srpska, dissolved
the parliament in July, and called early elections after opponents
rejected her demand to dismiss Interior Minister Dragan Kijac.
</P>
<P>
The OSCE, founded in 1975, is the sole organization which
includes all European countries, the United States and Canada.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
