<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AL Holds Israel Responsible for Violence Outbreak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Arab League (AL) General
Secretariat today lashed out at the Israeli decisions and coercive
measures regarding the Mideast peace process, saying they violate
the international laws.
</P>
<P>
The 22-member Cairo-based AL blamed the escalation of tensions
and outbreak of violence in the Mideast on Israel, whose policies
have breached "the Geneva Human Rights Convention and the
principles and accords which constitute the ground of the peace
process."
</P>
<P>
"These measures are aimed to starve them (the Palestinians) out
and undermine their power of resistance," said a communique issued
by the AL Secretariat here today, referring to Israel's three-week
economic sanctions and overall closure in the Palestinian areas
since the July 30 Jerusalem bombings.
</P>
<P>
Marking the 28th anniversary of the arson at Al Aqsa Mosque,
the communique said that the memory coincides with the Israeli
indiscriminate collective punishment and siege on the Palestinians
and their national authority.
</P>
<P>
On August 21, 1969, a group of Jewish extremists set fire to
the Islamic holy shrine Al Aqsa Mosque in East Jerusalem, arousing
Palestinian areas since the July 30 Jerusalem bombings.
</P>
<P>
"The ultimate end of the Arab nations is to establish just and
comprehensive peace that is based on restoring their legitimate
rights," the Arab League added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
