<HEADLINE> Death for Viet Drug Trafficker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Hanoi People's Court today
handed down a death sentence to a drug trafficker after a two-day
trial.
</P>
<P>
Le Van Minh, 28, was arrested by the police for trafficking
1.24 kilograms of heroin.
</P>
<P>
Under Vietnam's present penal code, anyone convicted of selling
or trafficking more than 100 grams of heroin or cocaine can
receive the death penalty.
</P>
<P>
The court also gave a life imprisonment sentence to a 20
year-old woman, who confessed that she and her husband, who has
fled, were involved in drug trafficking. According to the court,
the couple had smuggled 1.05 kilogram of heroin.
</P>
<P>
Hoang Van Hien, 28, another member of the ring, was convicted
of trafficking 190 grams of heroin and received a 14-year prison
sentence.
</P>
<P>
The Hanoi People's Court in May this year handed down death
sentences to eight people involved in Vietnam's biggest yet drug
trafficking ring, which was said to have brought several hundred
kilograms of heroin in Vietnam since 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
