<HEADLINE> Nicaraguans in Costa Rica Send Money Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Nicaraguans in Costa Rica send
home about 200 million U.S. dollars a year, the National Bank of
Costa Rica said today.
</P>
<P>
The figure exceeds the annual trade between the two countries
by 150 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Such a large amount of remittances may affect the country's
economy, according to the Costa Rican Central Bank.
</P>
<P>
There are 300,000 to 600,000 Nicaraguans in Costa Rica,
accounting for 10 to 20 percent of the country's population.
</P>
<P>
Most of those people come to Costa Rica illegally to seek jobs,
as 75 percent of the Nicaraguan population live in poverty and 20
percent of the workforce are out of job. 
</P>
