<HEADLINE> Ling'ao Nuclear Power Plant Well under Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Ling'ao
Nuclear Power Plant in Shenzhen, south China's Guangdong Province,
is proceeding smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Wenxing, general manager of the Ling'ao Nuclear Power
Co. Ltd., reported that earthwork is progressing on schedule.
</P>
<P>
Zeng said the successful experiences and sophisticated
management expertise gained from the neighboring Daya Bay Nuclear
Power Station have ensured smooth and fast construction at
Ling'ao.
</P>
<P>
According to Zeng, overall preparations for construction of the
nuclear plant is scheduled for completion by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Ling'ao is located 1.2 km from the Daya Bay Nuclear Power
Station which is now in full-scale operation. Construction of the
Ling'ao plant, a major project scheduled for completion during the
Ninth Five-Year Plan Period (1996-2000), began at the end of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of the Power Industry, Guangdong Province and the
China National Nuclear Power Industrial Corp. are jointly funding
the project.
</P>
<P>
Plans call for the installation of four nuclear power
generating units with a generating capacity of one million kw
each. Two units will be installed during the first phase of
construction at a cost of four billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The first generator will go into commercial operation in
July 2002 and the second, in March 2003. 
</P>
</TEXT>
