<HEADLINE> More Guangzhou-Wuyi Flights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Two regularly scheduled air
flights from Guangdong Province to scenic Wuyi Mountains will be
added later this month to cope with the increasing air passenger
volume.
</P>
<P>
Existing flights from major cities such as Guangzhou, Beijing,
Shanghai, Xiamen and Shantou fall short of demand as increasing
numbers of tourists flock to Wuyi Mountains. For example, no
ticket are available through the end of August for Guangzhou-Wuyi
flights.
</P>
<P>
Monday and Thursday flights will be added to the Guangzhou-Wuyi
route to supplement the current Wednesday and Sunday flights.
</P>
<P>
Wuyi Mountains are located in the northern section of coastal
Fujian Province in east China. Wuyi, well-known as the "first
mountain in Fujian", is the mainstay of the province's tourism
industry. Well over one million tourists visit Wuyi's each year to
enjoy its beautiful peaks, pools, and health resorts. 
