<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Businessmen Optimistic Over Congolese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 22 (Xinhua) -- There is massive business
potential in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, which the
Tanzanian business community can make use of.
</P>
<P>
David Mwaibula, President of the Tanzanian Chamber of
Commerce, Industry and Agriculture (TCCIA, made the remarks in
an interview with the local daily Guardian which is published
today.
</P>
<P>
Mwaibula said that restoration of peace in the new Congo has
unveiled enormous business opportunities for Tanzanian
businessmen.
</P>
<P>
The TCCIA president had accompanied Tanzania's former
President J. Nyerere during the latter's recent visit to the
Democratic Congo.
</P>
<P>
During the trip, Mwaibula met Congolese President L. Kabila
and discussed economic cooperation between the two countries and
the involvement of Tanzanian business communities in rebuilding
the economy of the former Zaire through trade, commerce and
investments.
</P>
<P>
Kabila reiterated the need for Tanzanian business community to
trade with his country and instructed Congolese business leaders
to visit their counterparts in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The TCCIA president believed it is high time Tanzanians take
advantage of Democratic Congo which has no proper financial
infrastructure and now is in the verge of rebuilding its ruined
economy.
</P>
<P>
Tanzanians can make a massive trade with the Congolese in
agricultural, livestock and industrial products and even by
investment in agriculture, communications and transport, he
suggested.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda and Uganda have already taken a leading role in
conducting business with the Congo, Mwaibula said. 
</P>
