<HEADLINE> Former Colombian President Pastrana Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Former Colombian president Misael
Pastrana, who had remained a leading figure of the Conservative
Party after he left office, died of intestine cancer today. He was
73.
</P>
<P>
Pastrana, who served between 1970-74, was the last president of
the so-called National Front, a power-sharing deal struck by
Conservatives and Liberals in 1958 to restore peace and stability
after a 10-year civil war in which some 280,000 people died.
</P>
<P>
President Ernesto Samper said in a statement that Pastrana
fought for Colombia's peace and prosperity all his life and would
be long remembered by his people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
