<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The following are highlights of
major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Premier Li Peng Thursday arrived in Malaysia on a
four-day visit of the country. This is the first leg of the
Premier's tour to two Southeast Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
-- Since the 14th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) in 1992, China's national economy has maintained a
high growth rate while inflation has been effectively
controlled. A frontpage commentary described this as "achievements
catching worldwide attention".
</P>
<P>
-- People in parts of east China's Zhejiang Province, who had
been hit by flooding caused by Typhoon Winnie for three days, were
evacuated to safer places, and have started to rebuild their
homes. Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, sent his regards to disaster victims
in Zhejiang.
</P>
<P>
-- A feature story outlined the changes that have taken place
in the appearance of Chongqing City, which became China's fourth
municipality directly under the central government in March this
year.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- The paper frontpaged an interview with an American
couple, who have visited China for 60 times and believe that "to
know China, one should go to the country to see with his own eyes."
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese and Japanese peoples should enhance the
Sino-Japanese friendship forged by the older generations, so that
they can live in permanent accord, Chinese Vice-President Rong
Yiren said yesterday in a meeting with the visiting governor of
Japan's Yamagata Prefecture, Kazuo Takahashi, in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
-- The Supreme People's Court of China announced yesterday that
three men convicted of selling fake value-added tax receipts had
been sentenced to death and were executed in Shanghai on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
-- China's Ministry of Public Security on Wednesday issued a
circular requiring police departments nationwide to further step
up the crackdown on prostitution and pornographic activities.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin Thursday met with two visiting US
senators in Beijing. Jiang told the American guests that China is
ready to work alongside the US to forge a long-term, stable
bilateral relationship for the 21st century on the basis of the
three Sino-US joint communiques.
</P>
<P>
-- China and Romania, whose natural habitats have suffered
during rapid economic development, agreed to co-operate in
environmental conservation.
</P>
<P>
-- The 10th World Conference on Tobacco or Health will be held
on Sunday through Thursday at the Beijing International Convention
Center. More than 2,000 scholars and health officials from around
the world are expected to attend. 
</P>
