<HEADLINE> U.S., Colombia, Ecuador Hold Naval Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Ships from the United States and
Colombian navies arrived in Ecuador today for a three-day joint
naval exercise with Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and Colombian ships arrived at the port of Manta, in
the western province of Manabi.
</P>
<P>
The maneuvers include exercise in continental defense including
anti-aircraft, submarine, surface, and electronic warfare, said an
Ecuadoran Navy spokesmen.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. fleet includes the destroyer Grasse, the missile
frigate Drewert, the landing ship Whidbey Islanda, and the
nuclear-powered submarine Sanlance, and will be under the command
of John T. Lyons, head of the South Atlantic Naval Force.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian Navy will take part with a corvette, a patrol
boat, and the submarine Tayrona, and its fleet will be commanded
by Rear Admiral Mauricio Soto Gomez.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadoran task force is under the command of Rear Admiral
Fernando Donoso Moran, commander in chief of the Navy Squad.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadoran fleet includes a frigate, squads of corvettes,
missile boats, a submarine, a Coast Guard ship, and personnel from
the Marine Infantry Corps. 
</P>
</TEXT>
