<HEADLINE> New Chinese Bank Reports Asset Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The asset value of the
Everbright Bank of China, a non-state commercial bank, has reached
51.1 billion yuan (about 6.2 billion US dollars), bank sources say.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Everbright, founded in 1992, had deposits
valued at 38 billion yuan in both the national currency and
foreign exchange by the end of June. Its outstanding loans were
worth 25.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Previously a subsidiary of the China Everbright (Group)
Corporation, Everbright last year restructured itself into a
joint-stock commercial bank with 131 shareholders, including the
Asian Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The restructuring resulted in an addition of 2.4 billion yuan
in the bank's capital stock, which has reached 4.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The ADB is the first international financial institution to
have an equity investment in a Chinese commercial bank. Everbright
also includes shareholders in finance, construction, chemicals,
tobacco, transportation, energy, steel, commerce and trade.
</P>
<P>
Everbright to date has set up 11 branches and sub-branches in
China's major cities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
