<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Railway Line on Plateau Becomes Modernized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Heavy financial input has
upgraded the Qinghai-Tibet Railway line, a link between the
plateau province of Qinghai in northwest China and the Tibet
Autonomous Region in southwest China, into a modernized railway
line.
</P>
<P>
To complete the project, the railway bureau in Xining, the
capital of Qinghai Province, has injected tens of millions of yuan
into the the rail line, which is 3,000 meters above sea level.
</P>
<P>
It has put nearly 20 million yuan into the modernization of the
trains on the line in recent two years.
</P>
<P>
The bureau replaced all steam locomotives on the line with
diesel locomotive in 1995, and used more than one million yuan to
equip some trains with an operation monitoring device.
</P>
<P>
Technological upgrading has enabled the railway bureau to
record safety statistics for a record period of time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
