<HEADLINE> Bortolami Wins Bernocchi Cup Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Former World Cup title holder
Gianluca Bortolami from Milan won the 79th Bernocchi Cup cycling
race in Legnano on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Bortolami came home 42 seconds clear of fellow Italians
Stefano Zanini and Marco Lietti.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's victory follows a recent upturn for Bortolami, who
was fifth at San Sebastian and third at Rochester. His career had
been dogged by injuries and accidents in the wake of his World Cup
success in 1994. 
</P>
