<HEADLINE> Chang and Ivanisevic Advance in Hamlet Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York, August 21 (Xinhua) -- World number two Michael Chang
and second seed Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia advanced to the
quarterfinals of the ATP Hamlet Cup in greatly different styles
here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Chang brushed aside Australian Todd Woodbridge 6-0, 6-2 while
Ivanisevic sweated to get past Ecuador's Nicolas Lapentti 5-7,
6-2, 7-6 (7/4) in their first-ever meeting.
</P>
<P>
Chang will next face Australia's Patrick Rafter, the eighth
seed who eliminated Czech Bohdan Ulihrach, 7-5, 7-5 and Ivanisevic
will on Friday take on Julian Alonso of Spain, who beat Sweden's
Jonas Bjorkman 6-3, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Fourth seed and French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil
was upset by Germany's Marc-Kevin Goellner, 6-3, 7-6 (7/3).
</P>
