<HEADLINE> Dow Slides 127 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 21 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks ended up their
three-day consecutive recovery today, with the Dow Jones
industrial average undergoing an unprecedented volatility and
plummeting at the end.
</P>
<P>
The Dow was down nearly 175 points just 15 minutes before the
close, but quickly regained about 50 points to finish at 7,893.95,
down 127.28. The drop snapped a three-day streak of 100-point
gains that briefly erased Friday's 247-point slide.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by more than a 2-to-1
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 497.56
million shares as against 518.15 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 14.31 to 925.04, and
the NYSE composite index fell 5.94 to 479.76.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 21.34 to 1,607.36, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index fell 0.20 to 646.56
</P>
<P>
Broad-market indicators, many of which had already surged about
4 percent this week, also retreated sharply.
</P>
<P>
Stocks were pressured from the open by a weak bond market,
where interest rates rose. 
</P>
</TEXT>
