<HEADLINE> Key Anti-Taliban Leader Killed in Air Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A key leader in Afghanistan's
anti-Taliban alliance, Abdulrahim Ghaforzai, has been killed in an
air crash, reports reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
Ghaforzai, who was selected as the "prime minister" of the
northern alliance only last week, was killed Thursday evening on
his way to central Bamyan province when his plane lost control
and crashed, the reports quoted an alliance spokesman as saying.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman described Ghaforzai's death as a "disaster" for
efforts to oust the Islamic Taliban militia from the Afghan
capital Kabul, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, street battles have reportedly broken out late
Thursday in the alliance's stronghold Mazar-e-Sharif, about 300 km
north of Kabul.
</P>
<P>
Heavy fighting erupted in the city when troops loyal to Uzbek
warlord Abdul Malik attempted to disarm soldiers loyal to Rashid
Dostum, whom Malik deposed in a coup nearly three months ago.
However, no further details of the clashes were immediately
available.  
</P>
</TEXT>
