<HEADLINE> Chinese Gymnasts Snatch First Gold Medal at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Italy, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese men's gymnastics
team snatched the first gold medal of the 19th World University Games
at the Sports Center here on Thursday evening.
</P>
<P>
Consisting of five gymnasts, three of them national
champions, the Chinese team collected a total of 167.450 points from
floor, pommel horse, rings, vault, parallel bars and high bar events.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the competition rule, the classification has
been established by adding the three highest scores of each apparatus
from a team.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese team, which will participate in the forthcoming world
championships, took the silver medal with 165.850 points, followed
by the Romanian team with 165.550 points.
</P>
<P>
The fourth and fifth places went to the South Korean and the Cuban
teams. The host country Italy shared the sixth place with Ukraine
with an identical score of 160.350 points while the Hungarian and
Russian teams came in 8th and 9th positions respectively.
</P>
<P>
The men's team competition drew over 80 competitors from 19 teams.
</P>
<P>
Xiao Yinchun, coach of the Chinese team, said after the
competition: "It is very pleasant for us to win the first gold medal
of the Universiade for the Chinese delegation. Our gymnasts did well
in the competitions."
</P>
<P>
The four-day gymnastics competitions attract more than 160 gymnasts
from about 40 countries and regions. The tournament features men's
and women's team, all-around and individual events with a total of 14
gold medals on stake.
</P>
<P>
The women's team competitions will be held on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
