<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, Paris Down on Profit-Taking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe
ended mixed today, with London and Frankfurt closing with moderate
gains and Paris down 0.74 percent.
</P>
<P>
Britain's leading share index finished slightly higher, but off
session highs due to profit-taking and Wall Street's opening
decline today.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that a sharp rally in shares in British
Telecommunications provided a boost to the FTSE 100 index, which
was 19.6 points higher at 4,978.0 by the close.
</P>
