<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Loan for Uzbekistan Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today approved
a loan of some 75 million U.S. dollars equivalent for Uzbekistan's
water supply, sanitation and health project.
</P>
<P>
The project will support the design to reverse the severe
health and environmental damage caused by the degradation of the
Aral Sea.
</P>
<P>
It will help improve the health of the rural population of
Karakalpaskstan and Khorezm, two of the poorest regions of the
country, by investing in water and sanitation infrastructure.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
